Following the release of Joshua Sunday, popularly known as De General by the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), the Nigerian comedian, has said he is not a drug trafficker. De General stated this in a new video shared on his Instagram page after he regained freedom from detention. He said, ”As you all can see, I’m alive, healthy, back in the house. I just want to debunk the news speculating that De General is a drug trafficker. Family Seeks Justice After A Nigerian Student Died A Day After… Gospel Singer, Sammie Okposo Takes Down Apology Post To His Wife… “I’m not a drug trafficker. If I was a drug trafficker, do you think they would allow me to go like that? I only traffic laughter,” he said. Recall that the comedian was arrested after drugs were allegedly found in his apartment.